    "evidence_quotes": [
      "The population pharmacokinetic two-compartment model successfully described intravenous levetiracetam pharmacokinetics in healthy adults.",
      "After combination with the oral pediatric population model, steady-state concentrations at the end of 15-, 30- and 60 min b.i.d. levetiracetam intravenous infusions in children were predicted to be 29—41, 17—24 and 6—13% higher than those observed after oral dosing of 30 mg/kg b.i.d.",
      "The combined model predicted that steady-state peak plasma concentrations and AUC␶ in children receiving 30 mg/kg twice daily as 15 min intravenous infusions were within the range of predicted and observed Cmax,ss and AUC␶ values of adults receiving 15 min intravenous infusions of 1500 mg levetiracetam."
    ],
    "notes": "The model was developed based on adult intravenous data and pediatric oral data. The two-compartment intravenous model parameterization allowed combining it with the one-compartment pediatric model of oral levetiracetam. The model was successfully qualified in children, as the predicted steady-state pharmacokinetic parameters matched those observed in adults."
  },
